wiki.summary: “Zen” is a promotional single by South Korean singer and rapper Jennie, released on January 24, 2025, as part of her debut studio album, Ruby, which came out on March 7, 2025. The track showcases Jennie’s vocal prowess and self-assuredness, blending a tribal beat with modern pop elements. The lyrics of “Zen” emphasize themes of empowerment and self-confidence. Lines such as “Nobody gon’ move my soul, gon’ move my aura, my matter” highlight Jennie’s assertion of her individuality and resilience. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: “Zen” is a promotional single by South Korean singer and rapper Jennie, released on January 24, 2025, as part of her debut studio album, Ruby, which came out on March 7, 2025. The track showcases Jennie’s vocal prowess and self-assuredness, blending a tribal beat with modern pop elements. The lyrics of “Zen” emphasize themes of empowerment and self-confidence. Lines such as “Nobody gon’ move my soul, gon’ move my aura, my matter” highlight Jennie’s assertion of her individuality and resilience. The music video for “Zen” features cosmic visuals and cultural symbolism, reflecting the song’s themes of empowerment and self-assurance. The release of “Zen” preceded Jennie’s album Ruby, which includes collaborations with artists such as Childish Gambino, Doechii, Dominic Fike, FKJ, Dua Lipa, and Kali Uchis. To promote the album, Jennie embarked on a short tour called the Ruby Experience, with performances in Los Angeles (March 6), New York City (March 10), and Seoul (March 15). Read more on Last.fm.
